theorem Topology.interior_closure_iterate_ten_eq_interior_closure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure
      (interior (closure
        (interior (closure
          (interior (closure
            (interior (closure
              (interior (closure
                (interior (closure
                  (interior (closure
                    (interior (closure (A : Set X))))))))))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- Collapse the innermost nine iterations using the existing lemma.
  have h9 :=
    Topology.interior_closure_iterate_nine_eq_interior_closure (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Apply the two-layer idempotency lemma after rewriting with `h9`.
  have h2 :=
    Topology.interior_closure_interior_closure_eq_interior_closure (X := X) (A := A)
  simpa [h9] using h2

theorem Topology.dense_iff_closure_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) ↔ closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    simpa using hDense.closure_eq
  · intro h_closure
    simpa [Dense] using h_closure

theorem Topology.interior_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : (x : X) ∈ A := interior_subset hx
  exact subset_closure hxA
